# 🎬 Basic Movie Recommendation System

A beginner-friendly data science project using Python to build a simple content-based movie recommendation system using a dataset from Kaggle.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project explores a movie dataset and builds a basic recommendation engine. The recommendations are generated based on:

- Genre and description similarity
- Cast/ director 

It’s a small project to apply core data analysis skills and demonstrate practical use of pandas, data cleaning, and basic recommendation logic.

---

## 🧰 Technologies & Libraries Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn *(similarity metrics)*
- Matplotlib 

---

## 📁 Dataset

The dataset was taken from Kaggle:  
🔗 [Kaggle Dataset Source](https://www.kaggle.com/discussions/general/281540)

---

## ⚙️ How It Works

1. Load and clean the dataset
2. Visualize the data to get some insight
3. Create a simple content-based filtering function:
   - Recommend movies with similar genres and descriptions



